*floor*

(PHP 4, PHP 5, PHP 7, PHP 8)

floor â€” Round fractions down

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  floor(int|float $num): float~

Returns the next lowest integer value (as float) by rounding down {num} if
necessary.

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{num}

  The numeric value to round

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

{num} rounded to the next lowest integer. The return value of floor() is still
of type float.

===============================================================================
[ Changelog ]

Version                               Description
8.0.0   {num} no longer accepts internal objects which support numeric
        conversion.

===============================================================================
[ Examples ]

Example #1 floor() example

<?php >
  echo floor(4.3); // 4
  echo floor(9.999); // 9
  echo floor(-3.14); // -4
<?>

===============================================================================
[ See Also ]

 * |ceil| - Round fractions up
 * |round| - Rounds a float


